<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Mississauga, Ontario 10/8/02 Stupid pack<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10198'>George "urthanz" Wilson</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10198&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 9, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Hey. I wrote another TR before, but this one had 2 more ppl! :) Anyways, this was a fun tournement. <br>
<br>
I woke up so early... So awake... Anyways, I decided to see if I had gotten any mail. I only got 1 of the 4 I was expecting... :( Anyways, that 1 was the Tale of gil-Galad :)<br>
So I worked on my deck... Decided that in order to be a big fellowship deck, I needed to use Gimli, SOG... I had already bought some Mines packs earlier on... Twilight Nazguls are popular at my tourney... So my deck was the best it could be... so I thought... So my brother gets there 10 mins. before the tournement, and we head out. We get there at 12:30 and since only 3 had showed up by then, we had a 3-way. This didn&#39;t count.<br>
<br>
My Fool&#39;s Gold Fellowship against Troy&#39;s Sack of Troy with arrows deck and Brook&#39;s Dwarven Combine deck (For all those who experienced the glitch on the site)<br>
<br>
I bid 0, my bro. bid 0, Troy bid 2! Troy starts Prancing Pony, and does it... He moves, and experiences nothing spectacular except my soldier who discards Sting! (Go Soldier). My bro. goes and he beats the little Soldier that discarded his patrol troop. Troy moves to 3, nothing special happens until Troy moves to site 4. I play Berserker and CYPMFY, and he takes 2 burdens (5) and Aragorn&#39;s exhausted! Berserker dies... at site 7, Brook meets the wrath of my soldier with an Ambition, and he&#39;s swarmed! Frodo dies! Me vs. Troy now. I go, nothing great against me. Very little happens in this game, except I jump to site 9 and take a win.<br>
<br>
+0! No points!<br>
<br>
Kyle Arrives. We start the duels.<br>
<br>
Me vs. Troy&#39;s Gondor to the Rescue!<br>
<br>
He bids 2, I bid 2. He wins, and goes. All this crap clogging my hand... I manage a few weak minions at site 4, then he stealths my bally twice, my fellowship is solid, and I stealth one, and cancel the other with Gandalf&#39;s Staff. He moves to 7, experiences a Sting-discarding Uruk Soldier and kills him. When he moves to 9, I manage a Troop and a Lurtz. I Hunt Them Down Troop and he&#39;s fierce for 1 twilight, due to Ambitions. I Spies for no archery. I then kill Legolas, Aragorn takes two wounds, Aragorn dies in fierce, and Frodo has 2 stealths and an Intuition.<br>
<br>
Good: Fellowship. Tale of Gil-Galad helped Legolas&#39; archery. Uruk-hai Armory kept my Uruk-hai alive!<br>
Bad: A loss. I was so close... except those cards in his hand.<br>
<br>
+1<br>
<br>
Kyle wins, and Troy wins, so they face off, and I face Brook.<br>
<br>
Me vs. Brook&#39;s my Patrol Troops are Coming deck<br>
<br>
We both bid 4, knowing that either of us have anything to be helped by burdens (except my Berserkers). He chooses for me to go first. I move, he puts out Armory and They Are Coming. He moves. He gets a taste of Soldier. He dies to Fror. I go. I meet nothing but a troop which Legolas (with Tale) kills in archery. He goes and experiences nothing. This is the hard part. My minions won&#39;t touch him, so I need to double-move. I move to 4 with 2 stealths in my hand. I kill the Patrol Troop with Legolas, watch as he puts out Swarms, and move again, to a useless bally and runner. Done. He goes and takes 1 wound on the souped-up Gimli. I hate Dwarrowdelf! He moves and I play nothing with 2 twilight! He moves again! I play bally which hurts 2 dwarves. Pretty much like this: I move to 8, and he plays 3 minions. I kill 1 with Legolas, and move again. I now have 6 fierce 11-15 power minions on me. Everyone dies except Merry, Gandalf, and Frodo. Frodo gets Overwhelmed. I lose.<br>
<br>
+1 (2)<br>
<br>
We wait. My games are always the quickest. Then I face Kyle. <br>
<br>
Me vs. Kyle&#39;s Twilight Nazgul without Nazgul!<br>
<br>
I bid 0. He bids 2. He goes to Prancing Pony. He gets out Aragorn... I have 2 in my starting hand. He moves to nothing except 3 Ambitions. I go. He didn&#39;t touch me with his Nelya. He goes. I have nothing. Stupid Heir to the White City! I go. I kill off Ostea with Legolas. He goes. I get out a few cheap minions and an Armory. I go with nothing. Little by little, things happen. Until at site 9, Kyle has Aragorn, Boromir and Frodo. I play Lurtz, Lieutenant, and Hunt Them Down (for 1) on Lieutenant. I think I&#39;m doomed. I kill Boromir and wound Aragorn. Second time, Lurtz is on Aragorn. I have my lieutenant with strength 9 vs. his strength 7 Frodo. Guess what happens? I lose!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
That is, until I discover that Frodo has the Rare Ring, 5 Burdens, 2 wounds, and I have Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry!<br>
<br>
+3 (5)<br>
<br>
So Brook lost. Brook, Kyle, and I tied. So Troy&#39;s friend comes, and we start a 5-way! This is how it goes: I lend my second deck to Troy&#39;s friend. Troy: 3 Kyle: 2 Troy&#39;s friend: 1 Me and Brook: 0. <br>
<br>
Troy starts. He moves a bit... I&#39;m the last one... I play Thror&#39;s Map! I get out like every good site. I also get Sting, so I remove that major twilight, and the Gaffer also comes out! And I play rare frodo! Nobody really does anything until site 5. Troy stealths both. His friend survives with power-ups on Gimli and ppl. Kyle loses Pippin and I think Gandalf. Brook survives, but kills Dwarf Guard. I stealth both. At site 7, we&#39;ve managed to kill <br>
Troy&#39;s Aragorn, Arwen, and Legolas. He ended up with only Frodo and Merry, with a fist-ful of minions. Everything happens normally... Kyle loses Everyone but Aragorn and Frodo at site 8, and Brook dies at site 8. I go, with 5 ppl. (Gandalf, Gimli and all hobbits but Sam. My other deck which Troy&#39;s friend was using used 4 enqueas which killed Legolas. Aragorn died at site 3 with a Blade Tip and Black Breath, and Boromir died to Such a Little Thing) I survive. So Troy also died at site 8. Troy&#39;s friend moves to site 9 with just an Attea. I didn&#39;t care, as he wasn&#39;t getting the prize. I saved my Lieutenant and Lurtz for Kyle. He won with my runner-up deck! Kyle moved, and put out Merry! I had no chance... The first time I killed Merry and Aragorn, but Lurtz had no pwer-ups on the 9 powered Frodo.<br>
<br>
+3 (8)<br>
<br>
So first of all, I HATE SUCH A LITTLE THING!!! Then, we opened the 3 mines packs only to find: Whip of Many Thongs, A Promise, and the great card Stricken Dumb! So I luckily ended up getting a Beneath the Mountains and a whip. And all I had to give up was 3 bucks and Staff Asunder! (Sarcasm) I had the chance to trade my Tale for Flaming Brand, Tower Assassin, and 2 Ranger&#39;s Swords. PLEASE tell me I wasn&#39;t wrong! this card saved me so many times! Anyways, here&#39;s what I have:<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
Troy for doing the tourney at his house.<br>
Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry for winning me the game!<br>
CYPMFY for helping me spot 5 burdens and exhausting Aragorn!<br>
Everyone for showing up.<br>
My second deck for winning.<br>
Brook for coming to a tourney! It&#39;s been so long!<br>
Brook for actually playing Dwarves.<br>
Kyle for playing an almost common fellowship side!<br>
Me for beating Kyle, who beat Brook, who beat me.<br>
Tale of Gil-Galad. That extra archery really helps.<br>
Remi Givogue for trading me PATHS and Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry<br>
Greg Byrne, Glenn Laird, Patricia Boetto, Paul Stafford, Debbie Roche, and many more for trading me good cards.<br>
<br>
Slops:<br>
Brook for almost eating Thror&#39;s Map.<br>
Me for losing so much! I normally win!<br>
Troy for playing a ranger deck. <br>
Kyle and Troy for always insisting on doing actions from 5 phases ago (including forgetting sanctuary stuff)<br>
Such a Little Thing. I Hate this card.<br>
Archers for ruining my day.<br>
People taking forever to think!<br>
Enquea for killing Lego.<br>
